version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-04-25
abstract: >-
  CARLA Studio is a Qt-based desktop application for the CARLA
  autonomous-driving simulator. It provides a graphical front-end for
  scenario authoring, sensor configuration, vehicle assembly, runtime
  control across Local / Docker / Remote / Cloud (Brev) backends, and
  integrations with TeraSim co-simulation, Autoware planning stacks,
  and the NVIDIA reconstruction-stack tools (NuRec, Alpamayo, AlpaSim,
  NCore, Lyra 2.0, Asset-Harvester). Studio orchestrates downloads,
  manages Hugging Face datasets and models, gates GPU-heavy operations
  via local-resource probes, and offers cloud-GPU offload via NVIDIA
  Brev. License: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
